quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
48,1,"(O Prophet), surely We have granted you a clear victory {1}",footnotes:1:When after the treaty of Hudaibiyah
48,2,"so that Allah may forgive you your shortcomings, whether earlier or later, {1} and may complete His favours upon you {2} and guide you to the Straight Way, {3}",footnotes:1:Here
48,3,"and that Allah may bestow upon you a mighty help. {1}",footnotes:1:Another translation can be: “Bestow on you an unprecedented victory
48,4,"He it is Who bestowed inner peace on the hearts of the believers {1} so that they may grow yet more firm in their faith. {2} To Allah belong the legions of the heavens and the earth; Allah is All-Knowing, Most Wise. {3}",footnotes:1:Sakinat in Arabic is calmness and tranquility and peace of mind. Here Allah calls its being sent into the hearts of the believers an important factor in the victory that Islam and the Muslims achieved at Hudaibiyah. From a study of the conditions of the time
48,5,"(He did this) to admit the believers, both men and women, {1} to Gardens beneath which rivers flow, wherein they shall abide, and to efface their evil deeds from them. {2} That, in Allah's sight, is the supreme triumph.",footnotes:1:That is
48,6,"(He also did this) to chastise the hypocrites, both men and women, and those who associate others in His Divinity, both men and women, and who harbour evil thoughts about Allah. {1} They shall be afflicted with misfortune, {2} Allah is wroth with them. He has laid His curse upon them and has prepared for them Hell. What an evil end!",footnotes:1:The hypocrites living in the suburbs of Al-Madinah were thinking
48,7,"To Allah belong the legions of the heavens and the earth. Allah is Most Mighty, Most Wise. {1}",footnotes:1:Here the theme of( verse 4 )has been reiterated for another object. There
48,8,"(O Prophet), We have sent you forth as a witness, {1} as a bearer of good news, and as a warner {2}",footnotes:1:Shah Waliyullah has translated shahid as a bearer of witness to the truth
48,9,"so that (all of) you may all believe in Allah and His Messenger, and support him, and revere him, and celebrate Allah's glory, morning and evening. {1}",footnotes:1:According to some commentators the verse means: “And help the Messenger
